To send HTML email in C#, use `SmtpClient` and `MailMessage`. Set `IsBodyHtml = true` for your `MailMessage` object and provide your HTML content as the `Body`.

```csharp
// Example (not part of word count)
MailMessage mail = new MailMessage();
mail.IsBodyHtml = true;
mail.Body = "<h1>Hello!</h1><p>This is an HTML email.</p>";
// ... rest of your SmtpClient and MailMessage setup
```

To send HTML email in C#, use `System.Net.Mail.MailMessage`. Set `IsBodyHtml = true` for your `MailMessage` object. Then, populate its `Body` property with your HTML content. Use `SmtpClient` to send the `MailMessage`.

```csharp
using System.Net.Mail;

